<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,362,1987,2013]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[227,930,2033,2060]" box="[227,930,2033,2060]" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">
After Latin ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[375,494,2034,2059]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Maccoyoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="35" pageNumber="102" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="concavum">
<emphasis box="[375,494,2034,2059]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="102">concavum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, referring to the shape of the venter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
